In this second JLGL collection featuring issues #13-24 of the twice-monthly series, the U.N. revokes Checkmate's charter, Captain Atom is wanted for murder, and Blue Beetle is . . . dead? Don't miss the second half of this can't-miss epic!
name: Vol. 2

description:
Wallflower Sweetheart

When did it all begin -- the afternoon I looked up from my desk and found Steve there -- the months previous, when I'd gotten to know his voice on the telephone? Or maybe years before in my romantic dreams when I'd wondered whether some place, somewhere there could be someone just for me!

The Headlines Between Us

There's always a story behind the headlines --- and no one can possibly know the heartbreak behind them except the person concerned. I am Joanne Brown whose name you have seen in headlines. And now I am going to tell you how it got there --- and why.

Cinderella To A Glamour Queen

Francine only gave away things she didn't want... Leila knew the man she loved still belonged to other girl.

Tricked By My Pity

It was Matt who set her aflame -- but it was Tod who needed her. Cherry knew no matter what she decided it meany an aching heart.

Also Numbered Vol.32 No.2
name: Cinderella To a Glamour Queen

description:
Penthouse In The Sky

Ever since I could remember, whatever luxuries came to us on our Midwestern farm, had been given us by Aunt Margaret and Uncle Tim. Aunt Margaret was mom's sister and she and her rich husband used to visit us each year. I couldn't help bragging about them -- their big car, their penthouse, and their generosity -- because they had made it possible for me to go to college. And it was at Cranston College that I met Frank Sanford and fallen in love with him!

The Kiss She Couldn't Forget

No Description

Two Loves Had I

I'm Sally O'Dea. I work in the chorus line of the "Candleglow Club" I suppose a pot of girls envy me. They think a chorus girl's life is pretty glamorous... and you might even meet a millionaire! Well, as it happens, I did! A real millionaire -- young and good looking. His name was Van Tinkersley and he wanted to marry me, because that's the kind of a girl I am... marriage or nothing! But I couldn't marry Van because of Gibs... Gibson Skinner, that is! Well, maybe I'd better tell you the whole story...
